# .github/CODEOWNERS
#
# Single-maintainer LTSC project — all paths route to @coo1white.
# This file's primary purpose isn't review-routing (there's only
# one reviewer) but to make GitHub render @coo1white as the
# canonical owner on every file's blame view, and to enable the
# `require_code_owner_reviews` branch-protection setting if/when
# the maintainer model expands.
#
# Path-specific rules below over-ride the catch-all when added.

# Catch-all: the maintainer is the owner of every path until
# explicit sub-paths reassign.
*                                       @coo1white

# Security-relevant surfaces — explicit pin so a future
# `require_code_owner_reviews: true` flip on `main` cannot let
# a reviewer with weaker auth (when the project gains a second
# maintainer) wave through changes to credential-handling,
# updater logic, or release scripts.
